#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "About bean references"
msgstr "关于 Bean 引用"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "When referencing beans using a string value in configuration properties, that string is parsed."
msgstr "在配置属性中使用字符串值引用豆时，会对该字符串进行解析。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Here are the most common formats:"
msgstr "以下是最常见的格式："

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`bean:` followed by the name of a `@Named` CDI bean.\n"
"For example `bean:myBean`."
msgstr "`bean：` 后跟一个 `@Named` CDI Bean 的名称。例如 `bean:myBean` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`class:` followed by the fully-qualified name of a class, to be instantiated through CDI if it's a CDI bean,\n"
"or through its public, no-argument constructor otherwise.\n"
"For example `class:com.mycompany.MyClass`."
msgstr "`class：` 后跟类的完全限定名称，如果是 CDI Bean，则通过 CDI 进行实例化；否则，通过其无参的公共构造函数进行实例化。例如： `class:com.mycompany.MyClass` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"An arbitrary string referencing a built-in implementation.\n"
"Available values are detailed in the documentation of each configuration property,\n"
"such as `async`/`read-sync`/`write-sync`/`sync` for\n"
"<<quarkus-hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch_quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy,`quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy`>>."
msgstr "引用内置实现的任意字符串。可用值详见各配置属性的文档，如 `async` / `read-sync` / `write-sync` / `sync` 代表 xref:quarkus-hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch_quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy[quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy] ."

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/2.16/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Other formats are also accepted, but are only useful for advanced use cases.\n"
